1
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:07,075
I've had enough!
Leaks in Red Hook, leaks in City Hall.

2
00:00:07,742 --> 00:00:09,824
You need to find them, Buck.

3
00:00:09,825 --> 00:00:11,117
Plug them.

4
00:00:13,867 --> 00:00:16,991
Whoever is leaking to the
City Without Fear site must be punished.

5
00:00:16,992 --> 00:00:19,824
Find out who it is, turn them over to me.

6
00:00:19,825 --> 00:00:21,949
It's my inside guy,
only he doesn't know it.

7
00:00:21,950 --> 00:00:24,783
If you are leaking stuff,
anything, stop.

8
00:00:24,784 --> 00:00:25,992
We could get hurt.

9
00:00:26,409 --> 00:00:29,158
Vanessa killed Foggy
and nothing happened.

10
00:00:29,159 --> 00:00:30,534
A line was crossed.

11
00:00:32,575 --> 00:00:35,158
Ever since Foggy died,
I didn't know who I was anymore.

12
00:00:35,159 --> 00:00:36,449
What I did,

13
00:00:36,450 --> 00:00:38,408
what that woman had me do,

14
00:00:38,409 --> 00:00:40,075
I had to get my mind back.

15
00:00:40,742 --> 00:00:42,616
One good deed.

16
00:00:42,617 --> 00:00:44,825
It levels the scales again.

17
00:00:50,117 --> 00:00:51,825
Wilson...

18
00:00:53,867 --> 00:00:55,784
Vanessa!

19
00:03:05,617 --> 00:03:07,824
I need blood pressure.
I need heart rate stat.

20
00:03:07,825 --> 00:03:09,324
- What's happening?
- Heart rate--

21
00:03:09,325 --> 00:03:10,449
- No, no, no.
- Sir, sir,

22
00:03:10,450 --> 00:03:12,241
- you cannot be in here right now.
- Get her!

23
00:03:12,242 --> 00:03:14,658
- Sir, you cannot be here.
- Vanessa. What is happening here?

24
00:03:14,659 --> 00:03:16,367
- Sir, sir.
- Vanessa!

25
00:03:17,367 --> 00:03:18,367
Vanessa...

26
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:22,824
- Sir, sir. Get back.
- Vanessa!

27
00:03:22,825 --> 00:03:26,366
Sir, sir. Mr. Mayor,
I understand that you are anxious,

28
00:03:26,367 --> 00:03:29,283
and we will get you all the information
as soon as possible.

29
00:03:29,284 --> 00:03:31,574
- Can you...
- Yes, yes. Okay. Sir.

30
00:03:31,575 --> 00:03:33,199
- Sir, please.
- Sir, please.

31
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:35,700
- Sir, please.
- Sir, let them do their job.

32
00:03:48,325 --> 00:03:49,574
All hands on deck.

33
00:03:49,575 --> 00:03:51,159
I need you to clear the schedule.

34
00:03:51,992 --> 00:03:54,866
- Yes! You need to...
- Like I said, absolutely no comment.

35
00:03:54,867 --> 00:03:56,866
How many times
do I have to tell you this, huh?

36
00:03:56,867 --> 00:03:58,033
I'm not gonna have to... I don't know when

37
00:03:58,034 --> 00:03:59,825
- a statement's gonna be ready, all right?
- Yes. Yes, go.

38
00:04:02,825 --> 00:04:04,034
If you have them...

39
00:04:06,617 --> 00:04:07,742
keep them alive.

40
00:04:08,159 --> 00:04:09,450
Uh, we don't, sir.

41
00:04:09,909 --> 00:04:10,909
Not yet.

42
00:04:11,950 --> 00:04:13,659
Pretty sure we have them surrounded.

43
00:04:14,659 --> 00:04:16,784
Sir, I want to find them as bad as you do.

44
00:04:17,034 --> 00:04:18,034
No.

45
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:20,700
You don't.

46
00:04:21,575 --> 00:04:22,659
You couldn't.

47
00:04:24,117 --> 00:04:26,159
Whatever you need, use it.

48
00:04:26,659 --> 00:04:27,659
You got it, sir.

49
00:04:29,325 --> 00:04:30,659
Officer Powell...

50
00:04:32,242 --> 00:04:33,242
Alive.

51
00:04:35,909 --> 00:04:36,909
Yeah.

52
00:04:42,450 --> 00:04:43,908
The tower is ready.
Have a seat.

53
00:04:43,909 --> 00:04:45,534
Let's move out.
Check that side.

54
00:04:53,742 --> 00:04:55,199
- Go, go, go, go, go!
- Over here.

55
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,325
- Here, here.
- Let's go.

56
00:05:04,075 --> 00:05:05,575
Prep towels, where are they?

57
00:05:07,909 --> 00:05:10,159
- Now!
- Whatever you need, man. We're with you.

58
00:05:11,534 --> 00:05:13,366
You don't have to do this.

59
00:05:13,367 --> 00:05:14,491
- Hold still.
- This is balance.

60
00:05:14,492 --> 00:05:16,158
- You know it.
- Shut up.

61
00:05:16,159 --> 00:05:20,116
Check in there. Check the door!

62
00:05:20,117 --> 00:05:22,409
- Do you have a boiler?
- Yeah, old shit back there.

63
00:05:23,450 --> 00:05:25,450
- Yeah, let's go.
- Leave me here.

64
00:05:25,950 --> 00:05:27,283
None of this matters now.

65
00:05:27,284 --> 00:05:28,659
It matters to me.

66
00:05:30,534 --> 00:05:31,866
Yeah, uh...

67
00:05:31,867 --> 00:05:33,284
No, no comment on that.

68
00:05:34,575 --> 00:05:36,867
I don't know when we're gonna have
a statement ready. No.

69
00:05:38,950 --> 00:05:39,950
Is she dead?

70
00:05:41,034 --> 00:05:43,908
What kind of sick
fucking question is that?

71
00:06:00,117 --> 00:06:01,533
How did you find me here?

72
00:06:01,534 --> 00:06:04,158
Seriously? I mean, how many hospitals
do you think there are, Daniel?

73
00:06:04,159 --> 00:06:06,199
- BB, you can't be here right now.
- Um...

74
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:09,283
- Actually, technically, legally, I can.
- BB, think.

75
00:06:09,284 --> 00:06:11,075
Nobody can know where she is.
It's... It's...

76
00:06:11,950 --> 00:06:14,491
The mayor's not in a good place.
You gotta go.

77
00:06:14,492 --> 00:06:15,574
Okay.

78
00:06:15,575 --> 00:06:17,825
I-- I get it. I'll go, but just tell me.

79
00:06:18,992 --> 00:06:19,992
Is she alive?

80
00:06:21,534 --> 00:06:24,283
Look, there's a ton of chatter out there.
You have no idea.

81
00:06:24,284 --> 00:06:25,699
It's, like, crazy right now.

82
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:27,992
And I just want to make sure
I get the story right.

83
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:32,825
We're really fucking
doing this right now, huh?

84
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:40,534
I... I'm so sorry.

85
00:06:42,117 --> 00:06:44,992
I shouldn't have come.
Just forget that I came, okay?

86
00:06:55,284 --> 00:06:57,034
She's in critical condition.

87
00:06:58,492 --> 00:07:00,825
They're... They're really lucky
to have you.

88
00:07:13,784 --> 00:07:14,784
Mr. Fisk.

89
00:07:17,367 --> 00:07:18,367
Mr. Fisk.

90
00:07:21,909 --> 00:07:22,992
Arash Merati.

91
00:07:23,825 --> 00:07:25,074
Happy to meet you.

92
00:07:25,075 --> 00:07:26,159
Dr. Merati.

93
00:07:27,159 --> 00:07:29,574
Please understand that
I am here to do whatever I can

94
00:07:29,575 --> 00:07:31,034
- for your beloved wife.
- Yeah.

95
00:07:31,534 --> 00:07:33,492
I had a chance to look over her chart.

96
00:07:34,284 --> 00:07:37,116
She is, as you know,
in quite a precarious position.

97
00:07:37,117 --> 00:07:38,117
Yes.

98
00:07:38,617 --> 00:07:39,992
I've heard that you're...

99
00:07:40,784 --> 00:07:42,534
the top man in your field.

100
00:07:43,325 --> 00:07:46,284
Well nothing is certain where the mind
meets the soul, Mr. Fisk.

101
00:07:47,034 --> 00:07:50,158
But that said, I will do
everything in my power for her.

102
00:07:50,159 --> 00:07:51,200
Thank you.

103
00:08:00,450 --> 00:08:03,241
Knowing what a disaster
Verizon is in Chelsea,

104
00:08:03,242 --> 00:08:07,950
I can only imagine what sort of
cellular joy awaits me in central Vermont.

105
00:08:08,909 --> 00:08:12,117
Hello.

106
00:08:27,409 --> 00:08:31,575
May I ask why you chose
not to include this piece tonight?

107
00:08:31,825 --> 00:08:34,408
I think it's pretty obvious
why I chose not to include it,

108
00:08:34,409 --> 00:08:37,950
but if you feel differently,
by all means, why should I put it up?

109
00:08:40,284 --> 00:08:41,284
I don't know.

110
00:08:41,534 --> 00:08:43,367
There's just something about it.

111
00:08:46,575 --> 00:08:48,158
Do you understand

112
00:08:48,159 --> 00:08:49,949
what keeps us in business?

113
00:08:49,950 --> 00:08:53,700
What pays for the cute little
gray shoes that you're wearing?

114
00:08:56,284 --> 00:08:57,659
But I can tell you...

115
00:09:00,450 --> 00:09:04,325
that if the right person
walks through that door

116
00:09:05,284 --> 00:09:06,950
and sees this painting...

117
00:09:08,409 --> 00:09:10,783
sees his own deep, inexorable,

118
00:09:10,784 --> 00:09:14,659
miserable emptiness
reflected right back at him...

119
00:09:15,909 --> 00:09:17,449
I can promise you,

120
00:09:17,450 --> 00:09:19,909
you can add two zeros to the list price,

121
00:09:20,659 --> 00:09:24,825
and it'll sell faster
than any other piece out front.

122
00:09:26,492 --> 00:09:28,200
The piece stays right where it is.

123
00:09:28,700 --> 00:09:31,325
Your call.

124
00:09:42,659 --> 00:09:44,033
I'm bleeding out.

125
00:09:44,034 --> 00:09:45,741
I've seen it enough times to know.

126
00:09:45,742 --> 00:09:47,492
I'm not interested
in your opinion.

127
00:09:48,700 --> 00:09:49,950
I've earned this...

128
00:09:50,992 --> 00:09:53,367
many times over. It's okay.

129
00:10:00,909 --> 00:10:02,159
You think she's dead?

130
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,200
I don't know.

131
00:10:06,784 --> 00:10:07,784
Come on.

132
00:10:09,075 --> 00:10:11,159
And if she is, it all balances.

133
00:10:12,742 --> 00:10:14,659
Your friend, Fisk's wife.

134
00:10:15,742 --> 00:10:18,284
Scales settled.

135
00:10:19,325 --> 00:10:21,825
- And I'm ready for judgment.
- Oh, good for you.

136
00:10:22,909 --> 00:10:24,159
You're not listening.

137
00:10:26,242 --> 00:10:29,492
That night you threw me off the roof,
I was supposed to die.

138
00:10:29,992 --> 00:10:32,242
Four-story. No one survives that.

139
00:10:32,909 --> 00:10:33,909
And yet...

140
00:10:34,742 --> 00:10:36,409
Maybe that's the grand design.

141
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,200
You're getting it.

142
00:10:40,409 --> 00:10:41,617
No, I'm not getting it.

143
00:10:42,992 --> 00:10:45,075
If she's dead. Vanessa.

144
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,366
That's just murder.

145
00:10:47,367 --> 00:10:49,033
Vanessa, Foggy--

146
00:10:55,450 --> 00:10:56,492
Don't say his name.

147
00:10:58,784 --> 00:11:01,075
You don't get to say his name.
Do you understand?

148
00:11:02,534 --> 00:11:06,283
- You--
- Tell me you understand.

149
00:11:06,284 --> 00:11:07,409
Don't say his name.

150
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:13,283
Even the best avocados
have to do grunt work.

151
00:11:13,284 --> 00:11:15,741
I guess we're gonna have to
break it to Josie that we're not

152
00:11:15,742 --> 00:11:18,200
- paying off the tab tonight.
- She'll understand.

153
00:11:18,659 --> 00:11:22,366
Lionel McCoy, 29 years old,
possession of multiple narcotics,

154
00:11:22,367 --> 00:11:24,241
including, but not limited to,

155
00:11:24,242 --> 00:11:26,491
Oxy, Moxy, Roxy,

156
00:11:26,492 --> 00:11:28,241
and wait for it, Xoxy.

157
00:11:28,242 --> 00:11:30,324
Christ,
guy's a walking pharmacy.

158
00:11:30,325 --> 00:11:33,283
Throw in a firearms charge, fake ID,

159
00:11:33,284 --> 00:11:35,575
intent to distribute,
obstruction of justice.

160
00:11:36,575 --> 00:11:38,949
Some yada. A little more yada
and yet another yada.

161
00:11:38,950 --> 00:11:40,658
And this guy is looking down the barrel--

162
00:11:40,659 --> 00:11:42,575
Wait, wait, wait. Okay, hold on.
Let me guess.

163
00:11:43,284 --> 00:11:45,492
I want to say 12 to 15.

164
00:11:46,242 --> 00:11:47,533
I'm sorry, Mr. Murdock.

165
00:11:47,534 --> 00:11:49,949
- The answer is actually 10 to 12.
- Oh, come on.

166
00:11:49,950 --> 00:11:51,908
- I was so close.
- But thank you for playing with us.

167
00:11:51,909 --> 00:11:53,658
And we do hope you enjoyed your stay

168
00:11:53,659 --> 00:11:56,283
in the correctional facility.

169
00:11:56,284 --> 00:11:58,324
Okay, what do you say?
Uh, we ask for six to eight,

170
00:11:58,325 --> 00:11:59,949
he's out in five for good behavior.

171
00:11:59,950 --> 00:12:03,908
Yep. Levine wants him to plead out,
so we take the best offer on the table.

172
00:12:03,909 --> 00:12:06,824
Under no circumstances
does this go to trial.

173
00:12:06,825 --> 00:12:07,908
Heard.

174
00:12:07,909 --> 00:12:09,033
After you, Counselor.

175
00:12:09,034 --> 00:12:10,575
Why, thank you, Counselor.

176
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:17,824
Good afternoon, Mr. McCoy.
My name is Matthew Murdock.

177
00:12:17,825 --> 00:12:19,825
- This is my associate--
- Foggy the Fembot?

178
00:12:22,075 --> 00:12:23,366
Ray?

179
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:25,324
You-- You know each other?

180
00:12:25,325 --> 00:12:27,699
Guy upstairs got a sick
sense of humor, don't he?

181
00:12:27,700 --> 00:12:29,159
We, um...

182
00:12:30,825 --> 00:12:32,700
grew up in the same building.

183
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:35,158
Isn't your name Ray?

184
00:12:35,159 --> 00:12:37,909
What, you think I'd go by Lionel
in that neighborhood?

185
00:12:38,450 --> 00:12:40,784
You know, Fembot,
he used to clean my sneakers.

186
00:12:41,825 --> 00:12:43,616
- Didn't you?
- Maybe we could refrain

187
00:12:43,617 --> 00:12:45,116
from the name-calling, Mr. McCoy?

188
00:12:45,117 --> 00:12:47,199
- What's with him? You blind or something?
- How--

189
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,241
How's, um, Connor?

190
00:12:49,242 --> 00:12:51,075
He moved upstate last year.

191
00:12:51,742 --> 00:12:52,950
Oneonta.

192
00:12:53,617 --> 00:12:55,949
I don't know.
Last I heard he was doing roofs.

193
00:12:55,950 --> 00:12:58,242
Some shit like that.
Gutters, maybe. I don't know.

194
00:12:58,659 --> 00:13:00,450
Knocked up the first chick he could.

195
00:13:01,492 --> 00:13:03,366
Okay, maybe we should, uh...

196
00:13:03,367 --> 00:13:05,159
Oh, yeah, please.

197
00:13:06,325 --> 00:13:09,658
We, uh, used to... hang out.

198
00:13:09,659 --> 00:13:11,574
Me and his brother, I mean.

199
00:13:11,575 --> 00:13:12,866
We were best friends.

200
00:13:12,867 --> 00:13:15,284
- The aforementioned Connor.
- Mmm-hmm.

201
00:13:15,700 --> 00:13:18,241
All right, uh, Mr. McCoy,
you're facing a laundry list

202
00:13:18,242 --> 00:13:19,741
- of state charges. I suggest--
- It's all bullshit.

203
00:13:19,742 --> 00:13:21,824
Regardless,
our firm was retained to represent you,

204
00:13:21,825 --> 00:13:24,117
and Mr. Nelson and I would like--

205
00:13:25,034 --> 00:13:26,034
You Mr. Nelson?

206
00:13:26,825 --> 00:13:28,784
- Is that supposed to be you?
- Foggy?

207
00:13:29,617 --> 00:13:32,283
You wanna tell your friend here what
the firm's professional advice would be?

208
00:13:32,284 --> 00:13:34,284
Yeah, yeah. Go ahead, Mr. Nelson.

209
00:13:35,034 --> 00:13:36,034
What do you got?

210
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:39,825
Right. Well, we, um...

211
00:13:41,492 --> 00:13:43,741
Given the charges,
the evidence against you,

212
00:13:43,742 --> 00:13:46,534
we suggest that you take a plea deal.

213
00:13:48,159 --> 00:13:50,408
We ask for a reduction in sentencing.

214
00:13:50,409 --> 00:13:52,450
And best case scenario, you're out in...

215
00:13:52,992 --> 00:13:56,074
- five to six.
- Or three to four with exemplary behavior.

216
00:13:56,075 --> 00:13:58,074
- Oh, five to six.
- Three to four if you...

217
00:13:58,075 --> 00:13:59,783
If, if, if, if, if I what?

218
00:13:59,784 --> 00:14:01,409
If I-- If I find God?

219
00:14:02,325 --> 00:14:04,783
Huh? If I-- If I mop the john?
Wait the library?

220
00:14:04,784 --> 00:14:06,908
I believe they call it rehabilitation,
Mr. McCoy.

221
00:14:06,909 --> 00:14:08,159
Mmm-hmm. You don't understand.

222
00:14:08,742 --> 00:14:10,992
The guys I work with want me dead.

223
00:14:11,992 --> 00:14:14,908
I mean, that's the whole reason
you two are even here in the first place.

224
00:14:14,909 --> 00:14:16,033
Cop a deal,

225
00:14:16,034 --> 00:14:17,325
they told you, right?

226
00:14:18,075 --> 00:14:20,784
No trial. Huh?

227
00:14:21,492 --> 00:14:22,617
You want to know why?

228
00:14:23,367 --> 00:14:27,783
Because they got about ten guys
on the inside just waiting to take me out.

229
00:14:27,784 --> 00:14:29,324
All right? That's how this ends.

230
00:14:29,325 --> 00:14:31,908
That's how this goes.
All right? So, it's not three to four,

231
00:14:31,909 --> 00:14:34,283
it's not six to eight
if I'm a little good boy. All right?

232
00:14:34,284 --> 00:14:36,659
It's 24 hours, counselor.

233
00:14:37,242 --> 00:14:39,659
I'm a dead man the second I go in.

234
00:14:40,367 --> 00:14:41,409
So...

235
00:14:43,242 --> 00:14:44,700
I'm not signing shit.

236
00:14:46,159 --> 00:14:48,199
I'll take my chances
with a public defender.

237
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:50,283
All right. Take it easy.
Back-- Back up here.

238
00:14:50,284 --> 00:14:52,534
What-- What are you talking about?

239
00:14:54,117 --> 00:14:56,450
You two don't even know
who you work for, do you?

240
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:08,825
This is Wesley.

241
00:15:11,450 --> 00:15:12,450
Right.

242
00:15:14,242 --> 00:15:15,242
I'll let you know.

243
00:15:19,534 --> 00:15:22,034
We may have an issue with the Lion.

244
00:15:26,992 --> 00:15:28,784
Are you familiar with Bitcoin?

245
00:15:30,867 --> 00:15:32,284
In light of the Russians...

246
00:15:35,242 --> 00:15:37,367
we should start diversifying.

247
00:15:39,325 --> 00:15:41,450
In this new world...

248
00:15:43,825 --> 00:15:47,950
we can no longer be old-fashioned
in our way of thinking.

249
00:15:49,242 --> 00:15:51,824
I do have some contacts
in the crypto space,

250
00:15:51,825 --> 00:15:53,616
but if I may, I would suggest

251
00:15:53,617 --> 00:15:56,659
it might be too volatile

252
00:15:57,242 --> 00:15:58,366
for our needs, sir.

253
00:15:58,367 --> 00:16:02,492
Hmm. Now, perhaps you have other ideas.

254
00:16:03,742 --> 00:16:05,034
Come to think of it,

255
