518
00:31:31,367 --> 00:31:33,159
What the fuck you doing here, Foggy?

519
00:31:34,867 --> 00:31:36,742
I know someone who can help.

520
00:31:37,325 --> 00:31:38,991
- A nurse.
- Nurses,

521
00:31:38,992 --> 00:31:40,575
doctors...

522
00:31:41,409 --> 00:31:42,575
lawyers.

523
00:31:43,367 --> 00:31:45,867
Vigilantes, assassins.

524
00:31:46,784 --> 00:31:49,034
Killing people, saving people.

525
00:31:51,659 --> 00:31:53,367
Act like it makes a difference.

526
00:31:55,075 --> 00:31:56,700
Like it matters at all.

527
00:31:58,450 --> 00:31:59,784
I wanted to give you this.

528
00:32:03,034 --> 00:32:04,034
The hell is this?

529
00:32:04,617 --> 00:32:07,659
I was hoping you'd take that,
and, I don't know...

530
00:32:09,117 --> 00:32:10,199
get out of here.

531
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:11,867
I don't even know where, but...

532
00:32:12,409 --> 00:32:13,949
Wait, wait, wait. So you--

533
00:32:13,950 --> 00:32:15,659
- You gonna give me money?
- No.

534
00:32:16,534 --> 00:32:18,700
Ray, I already gave it to you.

535
00:32:19,367 --> 00:32:22,367
What I want is for you
to start over with it.

536
00:32:22,867 --> 00:32:24,575
You got a second chance here.

537
00:32:25,034 --> 00:32:27,325
It's not about them. It's about you.

538
00:32:29,242 --> 00:32:30,242
About me.

539
00:32:32,367 --> 00:32:33,492
Just people...

540
00:32:36,325 --> 00:32:37,325
and, brother...

541
00:32:38,867 --> 00:32:41,366
we are who we are.

542
00:32:44,909 --> 00:32:46,200
You know those nights...

543
00:32:47,034 --> 00:32:48,034
we used to, uh...

544
00:32:49,409 --> 00:32:51,742
crash in the living room. Um...

545
00:32:53,409 --> 00:32:54,741
Well, you and Connor

546
00:32:54,742 --> 00:32:57,699
with the, uh, sleeping bags and...

547
00:32:57,700 --> 00:33:00,200
...uh, the flashlights, you know?

548
00:33:02,784 --> 00:33:05,242
I never really, uh,
had a friend like that.

549
00:33:06,909 --> 00:33:07,909
I know.

550
00:33:11,284 --> 00:33:12,950
We're all doing the same thing here.

551
00:33:14,742 --> 00:33:17,617
Acting something out,
scratching some kinda itch.

552
00:33:18,992 --> 00:33:20,284
But the worst part...

553
00:33:22,034 --> 00:33:23,825
is when you think you got it beat.

554
00:33:24,950 --> 00:33:26,034
You think...

555
00:33:27,200 --> 00:33:28,534
"I outran it."

556
00:33:31,492 --> 00:33:33,450
Then you turn the corner, bam...

557
00:33:35,742 --> 00:33:36,825
there it is...

558
00:33:38,575 --> 00:33:40,284
staring you right in the face.

559
00:33:42,784 --> 00:33:44,367
Only it's worse this time.

560
00:33:47,367 --> 00:33:48,409
And, you know...

561
00:33:51,659 --> 00:33:53,450
it was always gonna be there.

562
00:33:54,325 --> 00:33:55,784
Hey, do me a favor, will you?

563
00:33:56,409 --> 00:33:58,367
Tell my brother to stay
right where he's at.

564
00:33:59,825 --> 00:34:02,534
All right? You tell him
I told you to tell him that,

565
00:34:03,075 --> 00:34:05,117
that he ain't got nothing
back here for him.

566
00:34:08,075 --> 00:34:09,159
He's got you.

567
00:34:16,242 --> 00:34:18,242
Come on, Foggy. You gotta go, man.
Get out of here.

568
00:34:22,659 --> 00:34:24,159
There's no escaping it.

569
00:34:30,867 --> 00:34:32,409
I'm sorry to interrupt.

570
00:34:32,784 --> 00:34:35,159
This church will always provide shelter

571
00:34:35,825 --> 00:34:37,117
to both of you, but...

572
00:34:38,617 --> 00:34:40,409
I think they know you're here.

573
00:34:46,992 --> 00:34:48,449
Good evening, officers.
How can I help you?

574
00:34:48,450 --> 00:34:49,741
Hello, Father.

575
00:34:49,742 --> 00:34:52,658
You haven't by chance seen a couple of
vigilantes this fine evening, have you?

576
00:34:52,659 --> 00:34:55,992
I've been in prayers all afternoon,
Officer. I... I don't believe I have.

577
00:35:04,909 --> 00:35:07,200
Listen, we gotta come check the place out.
Mayor's orders.

578
00:35:09,450 --> 00:35:10,450
Just...

579
00:35:11,492 --> 00:35:12,575
go.

580
00:35:13,742 --> 00:35:15,034
Don't be an idiot.

581
00:35:15,700 --> 00:35:16,825
Leave me.

582
00:35:17,242 --> 00:35:20,241
Oh, I'm sorry, but weapons are not
permitted in the house of God.

583
00:35:20,242 --> 00:35:21,617
The rules have changed.

584
00:35:22,492 --> 00:35:24,242
Come on in, boys. Sweep it!

585
00:35:25,575 --> 00:35:26,909
I killed your friend...

586
00:35:27,284 --> 00:35:28,284
Foggy.

587
00:35:28,742 --> 00:35:30,117
I didn't think twice.

588
00:35:30,617 --> 00:35:32,241
That's who I am.

589
00:35:37,700 --> 00:35:39,117
Just let me die.

590
00:35:41,284 --> 00:35:42,284
I don't...

591
00:35:44,992 --> 00:35:46,491
Look, I can't save us both.

592
00:35:46,492 --> 00:35:47,909
I'm sorry. I tried.

593
00:35:53,367 --> 00:35:55,117
Let's go! Let's go!

594
00:35:56,409 --> 00:35:58,992
Sir! Let's go. Move!

595
00:36:01,325 --> 00:36:02,950
Imagine my surprise...

596
00:36:04,159 --> 00:36:07,074
when I came back to the office
and found the empty book.

597
00:36:07,075 --> 00:36:08,241
How did you know?

598
00:36:08,242 --> 00:36:10,991
Spend enough time in the same tiny office
with the same person,

599
00:36:10,992 --> 00:36:12,450
you tend to know what they're thinking.

600
00:36:19,117 --> 00:36:20,117
I'm sorry.

601
00:36:22,284 --> 00:36:23,533
I'll pay it back.

602
00:36:27,075 --> 00:36:29,034
Foggy the Fembot.

603
00:36:29,950 --> 00:36:32,491
And there I was thinking
the Murdock and Nelson fund

604
00:36:32,492 --> 00:36:34,325
was supposed to be about the future.

605
00:36:35,367 --> 00:36:36,867
It is, Matt.

606
00:36:38,784 --> 00:36:40,159
But not just ours.

607
00:36:44,950 --> 00:36:45,950
So, where to now?

608
00:36:47,034 --> 00:36:48,824
- Josie's.
- Obviously.

609
00:36:48,825 --> 00:36:49,950
What are we celebrating?

610
00:36:52,409 --> 00:36:53,534
Mercy.

611
00:37:12,200 --> 00:37:13,200
Fuck.

612
00:37:15,784 --> 00:37:16,950
Where'd he go?

613
00:37:35,909 --> 00:37:37,659
You really don't have to do this, man.

614
00:37:40,659 --> 00:37:42,741
I don't even know what I did.
But whatever it was,

615
00:37:42,742 --> 00:37:44,992
it was probably stupid,
and I probably deserve it.

616
00:37:46,075 --> 00:37:47,700
But I could just walk away, man.

617
00:37:48,492 --> 00:37:50,324
I could just disa-fucking-ppear,

618
00:37:50,325 --> 00:37:53,617
and you wouldn't hear anything from me.
Not a peep, not a tweet. Nothing.

619
00:37:55,575 --> 00:37:58,534
Man, I'd be like-- I'd be like Casper.
I mean, I'd be like a ghost.

620
00:38:04,950 --> 00:38:06,450
Look, I didn't fucking leak it.

621
00:38:07,242 --> 00:38:08,242
It wasn't me.

622
00:38:11,575 --> 00:38:12,575
I promise.

623
00:38:14,867 --> 00:38:16,325
Get out of the car, Daniel.

624
00:38:27,492 --> 00:38:28,492
Delivery.

625
00:38:46,575 --> 00:38:47,825
I like you, Daniel.

626
00:38:49,284 --> 00:38:50,409
I really do.

627
00:38:51,492 --> 00:38:53,617
But we work for a man
who can change your life.

628
00:38:55,367 --> 00:38:56,617
Has changed your life.

629
00:38:58,117 --> 00:38:59,617
And all he asks in return...

630
00:39:00,700 --> 00:39:01,700
is loyalty.

631
00:39:03,034 --> 00:39:04,117
Unbridled,

632
00:39:04,825 --> 00:39:06,117
unquestioned...

633
00:39:06,992 --> 00:39:08,659
- loyalty.
- Well, I've been loyal.

634
00:39:09,367 --> 00:39:10,909
I've stayed loyal, Buck.

635
00:39:12,617 --> 00:39:13,825
I'll do anything.

636
00:39:15,075 --> 00:39:17,991
I've said it before.
I'll do whatever it takes.

637
00:39:17,992 --> 00:39:19,075
Please.

638
00:39:20,950 --> 00:39:21,992
Make a choice.

639
00:39:29,284 --> 00:39:30,284
Saw...

640
00:39:30,950 --> 00:39:32,325
or shovel.

641
00:39:53,700 --> 00:39:54,867
You know, I was thinking.

642
00:39:56,117 --> 00:39:57,824
Maybe, uh,

643
00:39:57,825 --> 00:39:59,700
instead of Murdock and Nelson,

644
00:40:00,159 --> 00:40:02,784
maybe it's Nelson and Murdock.

645
00:40:03,950 --> 00:40:05,366
- I like that.
- Yeah?

646
00:40:05,367 --> 00:40:06,449
I bumped you up.

647
00:40:06,450 --> 00:40:08,074
- I love that.
- You're goin' up in the world, buddy.

648
00:40:08,075 --> 00:40:09,824
I am going up in the world.

649
00:40:09,825 --> 00:40:12,533
And I think the next 50 rounds are on you.

650
00:40:12,534 --> 00:40:14,574
I don't know about 50.
Fifty sounds a little...

651
00:40:14,575 --> 00:40:16,783
- Forty-nine. Sold.
- Forty-seven.

652
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:40,699
Little help?

653
00:41:03,784 --> 00:41:05,117
Vanessa.

654
00:41:05,617 --> 00:41:06,741
You're here.

655
00:41:06,742 --> 00:41:08,325
Yes, I'm here.

656
00:41:09,700 --> 00:41:11,325
I'm right here.

657
00:41:12,325 --> 00:41:13,950
It's so good to see you.

658
00:41:15,075 --> 00:41:17,325
Why are you acting so strange?

659
00:41:17,992 --> 00:41:18,992
Well, I... I...

660
00:41:19,450 --> 00:41:20,575
I didn't think... I...

661
00:41:21,575 --> 00:41:22,659
I didn't think that...

662
00:41:23,284 --> 00:41:25,367
You didn't think what?

663
00:41:29,784 --> 00:41:30,784
I just...

664
00:41:31,159 --> 00:41:32,409
I wasn't...

665
00:41:36,242 --> 00:41:38,284
I wasn't sure that I would see you again.

666
00:41:40,534 --> 00:41:42,616
That's absurd. I'm right here.

667
00:41:42,617 --> 00:41:44,325
Yes, of course. Of course you are.

668
00:41:44,617 --> 00:41:46,325
Yes, you are right here. Of course.

669
00:41:51,159 --> 00:41:53,324
What can I do? Can I do something for you?

670
00:41:53,325 --> 00:41:55,783
Are you thirsty?
Can I get you something to drink?

671
00:41:55,784 --> 00:41:57,658
Like water, or...

672
00:41:57,659 --> 00:42:00,199
Or are you hungry?
I can get you something to eat.

673
00:42:00,200 --> 00:42:02,741
Anything. I--
I could get anything you want.

674
00:42:02,742 --> 00:42:03,824
Yes.

675
00:42:03,825 --> 00:42:06,242
I'd like a pineapple juice.

676
00:42:07,075 --> 00:42:08,200
With ice.

677
00:42:10,284 --> 00:42:11,867
You don't like pineapple.

678
00:42:12,367 --> 00:42:13,367
I don't?

679
00:42:13,825 --> 00:42:15,033
No. Your-- Your lips.

680
00:42:15,034 --> 00:42:17,200
It-- It makes them tingle, I believe.

681
00:42:22,159 --> 00:42:23,699
Let's try anyway.

682
00:42:23,700 --> 00:42:24,909
- Mmm-hmm.
- Shall we?

683
00:42:25,325 --> 00:42:26,408
Yeah. Nurse?

684
00:42:26,409 --> 00:42:27,409
Nurse!

685
00:42:27,534 --> 00:42:28,616
Is everything okay?

686
00:42:28,617 --> 00:42:30,783
No. I mean, she's awake.

687
00:42:30,784 --> 00:42:33,574
Wait. She wants a pineapple juice.

688
00:42:33,575 --> 00:42:34,908
Sir, I need to--

689
00:42:34,909 --> 00:42:35,909
No!

690
00:42:36,825 --> 00:42:39,534
Pineapple juice in a glass, with ice.

691
00:42:40,700 --> 00:42:43,033
- Wilson.
- Yes?

692
00:42:43,034 --> 00:42:45,116
Why did you scare the poor girl? She--

693
00:42:45,117 --> 00:42:46,199
No.

694
00:42:46,200 --> 00:42:49,159
- You practically made her cry.
- No, I, I just... Um...

695
00:42:49,867 --> 00:42:52,284
I'm just overwhelmed, my love, that's all.

696
00:42:53,992 --> 00:42:55,158
Please.

697
00:42:55,159 --> 00:42:56,659
I've never seen you like this.

698
00:42:57,617 --> 00:42:58,950
I just thought that...

699
00:43:01,325 --> 00:43:03,741
I'm just glad you're with me here again.

700
00:43:03,742 --> 00:43:04,742
That's all.

701
00:43:05,700 --> 00:43:06,783
But...

702
00:43:06,784 --> 00:43:08,534
why did you think I'd gone?

703
00:43:08,992 --> 00:43:09,992
I don't know.

704
00:43:11,325 --> 00:43:12,325
I, uh...

705
00:43:14,075 --> 00:43:15,909
I just missed you so much.

706
00:43:16,367 --> 00:43:18,449
That's all. I just missed you so much.

707
00:43:18,450 --> 00:43:19,908
I missed you, too.

708
00:43:19,909 --> 00:43:22,909
- Yeah?
- I'm so glad to be here with you.

709
00:43:27,034 --> 00:43:28,034
Yes, baby.

710
00:43:40,867 --> 00:43:43,034
Is there something else you need, my dear?

711
00:43:43,909 --> 00:43:44,909
No.

712
00:43:46,409 --> 00:43:47,742
That was divine.

713
00:43:48,409 --> 00:43:49,409
Good.

714
00:43:52,659 --> 00:43:53,659
Wilson.

715
00:43:54,242 --> 00:43:55,574
Yes, my love.

716
00:43:55,575 --> 00:43:57,159
Will you tell me a story?

717
00:43:59,242 --> 00:44:00,367
A story?

718
00:44:02,034 --> 00:44:03,366
Yes.

719
00:44:03,367 --> 00:44:05,575
A story, please.

720
00:44:07,034 --> 00:44:09,284
What kind of story
would you like me to tell?

721
00:44:10,284 --> 00:44:12,409
Tell me the story of how we met.

722
00:44:14,700 --> 00:44:16,200
Oh.

723
00:44:23,242 --> 00:44:25,950
I've arranged for a more private
showing, but...

724
00:44:26,825 --> 00:44:27,825
this is it.

725
00:44:28,242 --> 00:44:29,409
This is the gallery.

726
00:44:33,159 --> 00:44:36,616
Somehow, I must have known
that you would walk

727
00:44:36,617 --> 00:44:38,992
through those doors and change everything.

728
00:44:40,325 --> 00:44:42,117
Lucky then, I guess, that day.

729
00:44:42,742 --> 00:44:44,534
Mmm, no.

730
00:44:45,159 --> 00:44:46,159
Not luck.

731
00:44:47,617 --> 00:44:48,742
Not luck at all.

732
00:44:50,534 --> 00:44:52,866
It was the grand design.

733
00:44:52,867 --> 00:44:54,742
Mmm.

734
00:44:56,075 --> 00:44:58,283
Though you did vastly overpay.

735
00:45:02,284 --> 00:45:03,533
Did I?

736
00:45:03,534 --> 00:45:06,116
Three times the listing price.

737
00:45:06,117 --> 00:45:07,658
I would have paid anything.

738
00:45:07,659 --> 00:45:09,784
That day was the...

739
00:45:10,492 --> 00:45:12,117
The deal of the century.

740
00:45:12,992 --> 00:45:13,992
Wilson.

741
00:45:16,575 --> 00:45:17,825
Yes, my love?

742
00:45:20,117 --> 00:45:21,825
Will you tell me a story?

743
00:45:22,159 --> 00:45:23,159
Please?

744
00:45:24,867 --> 00:45:26,534
Will you tell me a story?

745
00:45:28,325 --> 00:45:30,367
Can you tell me the story...

746
00:45:31,409 --> 00:45:32,617
of how...

747
00:45:33,825 --> 00:45:34,909
we...

748
00:45:41,075 --> 00:45:42,075
Yes.

749
00:45:44,825 --> 00:45:47,324
Vanessa.

750
00:45:47,325 --> 00:45:49,158
Vanessa.

751
00:45:49,159 --> 00:45:50,699
Vanessa!

752
00:45:50,700 --> 00:45:51,949
Vanessa!

753
00:45:51,950 --> 00:45:53,408
I need some help now!

754
00:46:52,659 --> 00:46:53,992
Well, hello there.
